                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="2va" to="169vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102732"> Johannes Merkelin </persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="desc">Sermons on the Sunday Epistles</title>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="2va" to="3va" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Prologue</title>
                                    <rubric>Prologus in exposicionem epistolarum dominicalium fratris iohannis merkelyn lectoris ordinis heremitarum sancti Augustini </rubric>
                                    <incipit>In christo reuerendissimo patri ac domino domino henrico diuina et apostolice sedis digna prouidencia warmiensis ecclesie episcopo frater iohannes merkelyn </incipit>
                                    <explicit>contemplandum qui est via veritas et vita valeatis feliciter peruenire</explicit>
                                    <note>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>: ruled, but no text.</note>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="3va" to="160vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Expositiones Epistolarum dominicalium</title>
                                    <rubric>Dominica prima de aduentu domini </rubric>
                                    <incipit>FRatres scientes romanos 13 gloriosus doctor beatissimus augustinus in epistola prima ad Ieronimum</incipit>
                                    <explicit>dignetur ipse rex glorie qui in eternum viuit et regnat Amen </explicit>
                                    <note>Begins with the First Sunday of Advent and ends with the Twenty-fourth Sunday after Pentecost.</note>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="160vb" to="169vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Index</title>
                                    <rubric>Vt legentibus in presenti libro prompcius occurrere valeant ea que in ipso continentur decerni tabulam immediate sequentem secundum ordinem alphabeti ordinare ad quam si quis voluerit habere recursum poterit illa que diffuse sunt in ipso tradita et in diuersis locis dispersa faciliter inuneire</rubric>
                                    <note>
                                        <p> Alphabetical index, keyed to the medieval foliation.</p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="170" to="170" scheme="folios"/>: ruled, but not text.</p>
                                    </note>
                                </msItem>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
